sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1159106
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PhyB(2-908 AA)_36AALinker_C-TEV-Protease (First part for a light-switchable TEV-Protease) in RFC[25]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This parts encodes are fusion protein consisting the photosensitive core of PhyB (2-908 AA) at the N-terminus and the C-terminal half of TEV Protease at its C-terminus. Both parts are seperated by a 36 amino acids long flexible linker. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix to allow further protein fusions.
Expressed with the second essential protein [http://parts.igem.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K1159315] or [http://parts.igem.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K1159315] containing the part which interacts with PhyB and the N-terminal half of the splitted TEV Protease, it form a light-switchable TEV Protease which is activated by red light and inactivated by far-red light.
'''''Note: PhyB requires Phycocyanobilin or Phytochromobilin as a cofactor to fulfill its function as photoswitchable protein; you can reach it by adding exogenous Phycocyanobilin/Phytochromobilin in the medium or by inserting genes for the Phycocyanobilin/Phytochromobilin synthesis. See here for more information: [http://2012.igem.org/Team:TU_Munich/Project/Light_Switchable_Promoter#Biosynthesis_of_Phycocyanobilin] '''''
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dong-Jiunn Jeffery TRUONG

The necessary N-terminal half can be found under BBa_K1159101. This part is flanked by RFC[25] pre- and suffix for further protein fusions.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a linker, it can be used to connect two parts and add additional space between these parts. That can be necessary to avoid interactions between these parts. The GSAT linker was create to connect our protein domains Fok_a and Fok_i to an function final construct.
